# PLAYBOOK.md — Organisation Configuration (Example)
# Org-level defaults for this expert. Lives in your private config overlay (never committed).
# Copy to ~/clawd/kung-fu-config/experts/[expert-name]/PLAYBOOK.md and customise.
# PLAYBOOK.md sets org-wide defaults. USER.md overrides for the individual.

## Company context
- Company: ~~company-name → Acme Travel Co
- Industry: ~~industry → Online Travel (OTA + B2B)
- Stage: ~~company-stage → Series C, 400 employees
- Primary markets: ~~primary-markets → Southeast Asia, Middle East
- Fiscal year: ~~fiscal-year → Jan–Dec

## Tools & stack
- Data warehouse: ~~data-warehouse → BigQuery
- BI: ~~bi-tool → Looker
- Project management: ~~project-tool → Jira
- Docs: ~~docs-tool → Google Workspace + Notion
- Communication: ~~comms-tool → Slack
- Finance: ~~finance-tool → NetSuite
- CRM: ~~crm-tool → Salesforce

## Standards & defaults
- Reporting currency: ~~reporting-currency → USD
- Date format: ISO 8601 (YYYY-MM-DD)
- Deck template: Google Slides (company template in Drive)
- Default output language: English (EN-SG spelling)
- Data sensitivity: treat all revenue and headcount data as confidential

## Decision-making
- Approval threshold for spend: ~~spend-threshold → >$50k requires VP approval; >$200k requires CEO
- Escalation path: Team Lead → VP → CEO → Board
- Strategy review cadence: quarterly (aligned to board)

## Communication standards
- Internal updates: weekly written update every Friday by 5pm local
- Exec presentations: 1-page brief + appendix for data; no wall-of-text slides
- Customer-facing: avoid internal jargon; lead with benefit, not feature
